library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
setwd('~/Documents/Projects/combine_clinicals/')

#Load in the data
#Urine data
atwell_urine <- read_csv('Atwell_urine.csv')
bouranis_urine <- read_csv('Bouranis_urine.csv')
clarke_urine <- read_csv('Clarke_urine.csv')

#Volume data
atwell_urine_vol <- read_csv('Atwell_urine_vol.csv')
bouranis_urine_vol <- read_csv('Bouranis_urine_vol.csv')
clark_urine_vol <- read_csv('Clarke_urine_vol.csv')

#Plasma data
atwell_plasma <- read_csv('Atwell_plasma.csv')
clarke_plasma <- read_csv('Clarke_plasma.csv')


#Sprout Data
sprout_data <- read_csv('sprout_data.csv')

Notes

  • John Clarke fed his subjects 40 grams of sprouts which were equivalent to 150 µMol of SFN

  • Lauren Atwell fed her subjects an average of 102 grams of sprouts which were equivalent to 200 µMol of SFN

  • Yanni Bouranis fed his subjects between 22 and 71 grams of sprouts which equivalent to between 81.3 and 161.7 µMol of SFN.

  • From talking to Carmen: The values for Lauren Atwell’s study may be artifically low due to the standard curve being out of rang, while John Clarke further diluted his samples preventing this problem.

  • Gram amounts for the Atwell study is the average mass fed, as different batches were fed to the different participants.

  • Yanni’s study didn’t include a 12 hour time point - The 24 hour time point in his study is essentially equivalent to 12 + 24 in the Atwell and Clarke studies.

a_vol_clean <- atwell_urine_vol %>%
  #Convert mL to L
  mutate(across(c(2:7), ~.x/1000)) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -subject, names_to = 'time', values_to = 'volume') %>%
  modify_at('time', as.integer)
  
b_vol_clean <- bouranis_urine_vol %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  #Convert mL to L
  mutate(across(starts_with('vol'), ~.x/1000)) %>%
  rename_with(., ~gsub('vol_','', .x)) %>%
  rename_with(., ~gsub('h$','', .x)) %>%
  modify_at('time', as.integer) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(4:9), names_to = 'time', values_to = 'volume') 

atwell_clean <- atwell_urine %>%
  dplyr::select(-SFNNIT) %>%
  left_join(a_vol_clean) %>%
  mutate(across(starts_with('SFN'), ~.x*volume)) %>%
  inset('Study', value = 'Atwell') %>%
  left_join(., sprout_data) %>%
  mutate(SFN_Tot = SFN + SFN_CYS + SFN_NAC + SFN_CG + SFN_GSH) %>%
  select(subject, time, starts_with('SFN'), g_sprouts, umol_SFN, Study) %>%
  rename('subject_id' = subject) %>%
  modify_at(c('subject_id', 'time'), as.factor)

bouranis_clean <- bouranis_urine %>%
  mutate(time = gsub('h', '', time)) %>%
  dplyr::select(-SFN_NIT, -SFN_Tot) %>%
  left_join(b_vol_clean) %>%
  mutate(across(starts_with('SFN'), ~.x*volume)) %>%
  filter(treatment != 'AL') %>%
  inset('Study', value = 'Bouranis') %>%
  left_join(., sprout_data, by = c(c('Study' = 'Study'), c('cohort' = 'Cohort'), c('treatment' = 'Treatment'))) %>%
  mutate(SFN_Tot = SFN + SFN_CYS + SFN_NAC + SFN_CG + SFN_GSH) %>%
  select(subject_id, time, starts_with('SFN'), g_sprouts, umol_SFN, Study) %>%
  modify_at(c('subject_id', 'time'), as.factor) %>%
  filter(!subject_id %in% c('BSS040', 'BSS037', 'BSS081'))
  
clarke_clean <- clarke_urine %>%
  #Convert from nanoMols to uMols
  mutate(across(starts_with('SFN'), ~.x/1000)) %>%
  inset('Study', value = 'Clarke') %>%
  left_join(., sprout_data) %>%
  rename('subject_id' = Subject_id, 'time' = Time, 'SFN_CYS' = SFN_Cys) %>%
  mutate(SFN_Tot = SFN + SFN_CYS + SFN_NAC + SFN_CG + SFN_GSH) %>%
  select(subject_id, time, starts_with('SFN'), g_sprouts, umol_SFN, Study) %>%
  modify_at(c('subject_id', 'time'), as.factor) %>%
  filter(!subject_id %in% c(46,82,88,355))

full_set <- rbind(atwell_clean, bouranis_clean, clarke_clean)
full_tidy <- full_set %>%
  pivot_longer(c(starts_with('SFN'), -'SFN_Tot'), names_to = 'metabolite', values_to = 'uMol')

Urine

Comparison of Studies over Time

Total SFN

ggplot(full_set, aes(x = time,y = SFN_Tot, color = Study)) +
  geom_bar(aes(group = Study, fill = Study), stat = 'summary', fun = mean, color = 'black', alpha = 0.5, position = 'dodge2') +
  geom_point(position = position_dodge(width = 1)) +
  ggtitle('Total SFN Metabolites') +
  xlab('Time (Hours)') +
  ylab('Total SFN (µMol)') +
  cowplot::theme_minimal_grid()

ser <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))

full_set %>%
  group_by(Study, time) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(SFN_Tot), se = ser(SFN_Tot)) %>%
  mutate(mse = paste0(round(mean, 3), '±', round(se, 2))) %>%
  dplyr::select(-mean, -se) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = 'time', values_from = 'mse') %>%
  knitr::kable(., caption = 'Average Total µMol SFN Metabolites Recovered at Each Time Point')

SFN_cs <- full_set %>%
  group_by(Study, subject_id, umol_SFN, g_sprouts) %>%
  summarise(cs = sum(SFN_Tot))

ggplot(SFN_cs, aes(x = umol_SFN, y = cs, color = Study)) +
  geom_point() +
  ggtitle('Total SFN Metabolites') +
  xlab('µMol SFN Fed') +
  ylab('Cumulative SFN Metabolites Excreted (µMol)') +
  cowplot::theme_minimal_grid()

SFN_cs %>%
  group_by(Study, umol_SFN) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(cs), se = ser(cs), n_participants = n()) %>%
  mutate(mse = paste0(round(mean, 3), '±', round(se, 2))) %>%
  dplyr::select(-mean, -se) %>%
  arrange(umol_SFN) %>%
  dplyr::select(Study, n_participants, umol_SFN, mse) %>%
  rename('µMol Fed' = umol_SFN, 'Mean ± SE (µMol)' = mse, '# Participants' = n_participants) %>%
  knitr::kable(.)

a_plasma <- atwell_plasma %>%
  inset('Study', value = 'Atwell') %>%
  rename('subject_id' = `Subject ID`, 'time' = Time, 'SFN_CYS' = 'SFN_Cys') %>%
  left_join(., sprout_data) %>%
  mutate(SFN_Tot = SFN + SFN_CYS + SFN_NAC + SFN_CG + SFN_GSH) %>%
  select(subject_id, time, starts_with('SFN'), g_sprouts, umol_SFN, Study) %>%
  modify_at(c('subject_id', 'time'), as.factor)

c_plasma <- clarke_plasma %>%
  inset('Study', value = 'Clarke') %>%
  rename('subject_id' = Subject_id, 'time' = Time, 'SFN_CYS' = 'SFN_Cys') %>%
  left_join(., sprout_data) %>%
  mutate(SFN_Tot = SFN + SFN_CYS + SFN_NAC + SFN_CG + SFN_GSH) %>%
  select(subject_id, time, starts_with('SFN'), g_sprouts, umol_SFN, Study) %>%
  modify_at(c('subject_id', 'time'), as.factor) %>%
  filter(!subject_id %in% c(46,82,88,355))

full_plasma <- rbind(a_plasma, c_plasma)
tidy_plasma <- full_plasma %>%

  group_by(Study, subject_id, umol_SFN, g_sprouts, metabolite) %>%
  summarise(cs = sum(uMol))

  ylab('Cumulative Excreted (µMol)') +
  cowplot::theme_minimal_grid() +
  facet_wrap(~metabolite, nrow = 3, scales = 'free_y')
